liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: ABC global affairs correspondent John Lyons is giving an interview from Ashdod in Israel now. Asked what obligation Arab nations may feel to alleviate the situation, he said: "The Arab world has this problem of, 'What do we do?'" "Do they get a UN-brokered temporary administration in there? "Does it then become a bit like Baghdad which becomes unwieldy and ungovernable, and then go into 10 or 20 years of insurgencies like we've had in Baghdad or in Kabul? So it is a real problem. "What do the Israelis want? If they do get into Gaza City and take it, what happens then?" We'll have video of that interview in full for you shortly.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: John Lyons speaks to ABC's The World

children.content: ABC global affairs correspondent John Lyons is giving an interview from Ashdod in Israel now.
Asked what obligation Arab nations may feel to alleviate the situation, he said: "The Arab world has this problem of, 'What do we do?'"
"Do they get a UN-brokered temporary administration in there?
"Does it then become a bit like Baghdad which becomes unwieldy and ungovernable, and then go into 10 or 20 years of insurgencies like we've had in Baghdad or in Kabul? So it is a real problem.
"What do the Israelis want? If they do get into Gaza City and take it, what happens then?"
We'll have video of that interview in full for you shortly.
